appendix.para:
To enable Multibyte Characters to work with the db:linkURL tag, you must



use at least java version 1.1.4



Add the following to org.dbforms.util:

import java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException;
...


public static final String encode(String s, String enc)
      throws UnsupportedEncodingException
   {
      if (!Util.isNull(s))
      {
         s = URLEncoder.encode(s, enc);
      }

      return s;
   }




Change Util.encode(position) in org.dbforms.DbLinkURLTag.doEndTag() to Util.encode(position,request.getCharacterEncoding ())



Change Util.encode(keyToDestPos) in org.dbforms.DbLinkURLTag.doEndTag() to Util.encode(keyToDestPos,request.getCharacterEncoding ())



Change Util.encode(keyToKeyToDestPos) in org.dbforms.DbLinkURLTag.doEndTag() to Util.encode(keyToKeyToDestPos,request.getCharacterEncoding ())



Rebuild DbForms via Ant and deploy the new jar.
